parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt system can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident, compromising the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to retract
the seat belt is stuck in the window
the seat belt does not automatically lock/unlock
the seat belt does not restrain the passenger
the seat belt buckle is broken
the threading of the shoulder harness breaks
the shoulder belt breaks at the stitching.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emergency brake cable can cause the parking brake to malfunction, leading to a loss of control or unintended movement of the vehicle, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The emergency brake cable locks up or freezes
the parking brake does not engage or disengage properly
the parking brake lever is difficult to adjust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake adjusters can cause the rear brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the vehicle vibrates or shakes while braking
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the front end of the vehicle to vibrate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle vibrates or shakes while braking
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.
